At the top is one of these ESP32 modules with a fisheye camera lens and an infrared LED that I salvaged from a Raspberry Pi device.
If this plastic box has an odd shape, it's because of the pivoting side panel of the birdhouse. I bought it like that and couldn't modify it, so I had to design my installation around it.
Since there is no electricity in the garden, the entire system is powered by a solar panel and a 2,600 mAh 18650 cell.
I didn't photograph the cell and the charger, but here is a photo of the panel.
The gray box hanging on the side of the birdhouse houses the battery.
When fully charged, it gives me about 4 hours of battery life.
I call it a feature. So that birds can also have a bit of privacy.
